  "prompt": "What are great questions to interview a salesman?",
  "response": "Here are some great questions to ask when interviewing a salesman:\n\n1. Performance and Track Record\n- What was your sales quota in your previous role?\n- What percentage of your quota did you typically achieve?\n- Can you describe your most successful sale?\n\n2. Sales Approach and Strategy\n- What is your typical sales process?\n- How do you identify and qualify potential leads?\n- How do you handle objections from potential clients?\n\n3. Skills and Experience\n- What industries have you worked in?\n- What sales techniques have you found most effective?\n- How do you build and maintain customer relationships?\n\n4. Motivation and Personality\n- What motivates you in sales?\n- How do you handle rejection?\n- Why did you choose a career in sales?\n\n5. Product Knowledge\n- How do you stay updated on product information?\n- How do you explain complex products to potential customers?\n- Can you give an example of how you've matched a product to a customer's specific needs?\n\n6. Situational Questions\n- How would you handle a difficult customer?\n- Describe a time when you turned a potential lost sale into a successful one\n- How do you prioritize your sales activities?\n\n7. Technology and Tools\n- What CRM systems have you used?\n- How comfortable are you with digital sales tools?",
